-- European Stocks, U.S. Index Futures Rise; BP Advances on Gulf Well Sealing
-- David Merritt
-- 2010-09-20T07:05:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-20/european-stocks-u-s-index-futures-rise-bp-advances-on-gulf-well-sealing.html

          
          
             European stocks advanced, snapping
a four-days decline for the Stoxx Europe 600 Index. U.S. index
futures and Asian shares also rose.  
 The benchmark Stoxx 600 gained 0.3 percent to 263.61 at
8:02 a.m. in London. Futures on the Standard & Poor’s 500 Index
rose 0.3 percent, while the MSCI Asia Pacific Index also
advanced 0.3 percent.  
 BP Plc rallied 1.4 percent after the company said it
permanently sealed its Macondo well in the Gulf of Mexico.  
          
          


  
     
       
     
           
                                                 
                     
